{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Biscuits","content":["Preheat oven to 450°F. Grease and lightly flour a square baking pan (9 in. x 9 in.).","Place flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder, butter and shortening into mixing bowl and mix <nobr>5 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr>.","Add buttermilk and bacon drippings (if using) through hole in mixing bowl lid and mix <nobr>2 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr> then knead <nobr>20 sec\/<\/nobr> to form a soft sticky dough.","Transfer dough onto a lightly floured surface (see Tip), dust top of dough with flour and gently press out to a 1 ¼ in. thick rectangle. Fold dough into thirds, flatten and fold again. Repeat until you have folded the dough 4 – 5 times.  Gently press into a 1 in. thick circle.","Dip a 2 1\/2 in. round cookie cutter into flour to prevent dough from sticking, cut out biscuits by pushing cutter into dough starting around outside edges and working towards center.  Gently press remaining dough together and repeat procedure.","Place biscuits on prepared baking pan so they are just touching. Bake 15-20 minutes (450°F) or until golden brown.","Wrap biscuits in a clean kitchen towel to keep warm before serving."]},{"title":"Gravy","content":["Place crumbled pieces of breakfast sausage, butter, flour, salt and pepper into mixing bowl and without measuring cup cook <nobr>8-10 min\/250°F\/\/speed <\/nobr>.","Add milk through hole in mixing bowl lid, insert measuring cup and cook <nobr>15 min\/212°F\/\/speed 2<\/nobr>.","Serve immediately over fresh warm biscuits."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Biscuits","content":["1 oz salted butter, cut into pieces and frozen, plus extra to grease","9 oz all-purpose flour, plus extra to dust","¾ tsp fine sea salt","¼ tsp baking soda","4 tsp baking powder","1 oz vegetable shortening, cut into pieces and frozen","7 ½ oz buttermilk, chilled","1 tsp bacon drippings, optional"]},{"title":"Gravy","content":["16 oz uncooked breakfast sausage, crumbled into pieces","2 oz salted butter","2 oz 